      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments cover the same device geometry, fluid, and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under CPB-representative conditions. Blood analog fluid (glycerin-water, 37% hematocrit equivalent viscosity) used. Operating envelope (2–6 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM) spans the intended clinical use range."
