      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law model selection documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "Not assessed at MRL 2; SST k-omega turbulence model and Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power law selected based on literature precedent. Formal model form assessment not required at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) documented with sources and uncertainty bounds. UQ performed over key input parameters.",
      "rationale": "Geometry sourced from FDA benchmark CAD files. Fluid properties measured in-house with documented uncertainty (viscosity ±2%, density ±0.1%). Boundary conditions derived from experimental measurements. Uncertainty quantification was performed using Monte Carlo sampling over inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity, yielding 95th-percentile bounds on NIH. A full sensitivity analysis identifying dominant input drivers is planned for the next revision of this assessment; the current UQ characterizes aggregate output uncertainty without ranking individual input contributions."
    },
